 &lt;p&gt;⭐️⭐️⭐️&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&#34;https://leetcode.com/problems/score-after-flipping-matrix/description/?envType=daily-question&amp;amp;envId=2024-05-13&#34;&gt;&lt;ins class=&#34;dot&#34;&gt;題目敘述&lt;/ins&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are given an  &lt;code&gt;m x n&lt;/code&gt;  binary matrix  &lt;code&gt;grid&lt;/code&gt; .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;strong&gt;move&lt;/strong&gt; consists of choosing any row or column and toggling each value in that row or column (i.e., changing all  &lt;code&gt;0&lt;/code&gt; &#39;s to  &lt;code&gt;1&lt;/code&gt; &#39;s, and all  &lt;code&gt;1&lt;/code&gt; &#39;s to  &lt;code&gt;0&lt;/code&gt; &#39;s).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Every row of the matrix is interpreted as a binary number, and the &lt;strong&gt;score&lt;/strong&gt; of the matrix is the sum of these numbers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Return &lt;em&gt;the highest possible &lt;strong&gt;score&lt;/strong&gt; after making any number of &lt;strong&gt;moves&lt;/strong&gt; (including zero moves).&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;example-1&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#example-1&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Example 1&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img data-src=&#34;https://assets.leetcode.com/uploads/2021/07/23/lc-toogle1.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;&#34; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input:&lt;/strong&gt; grid = [[0,0,1,1],[1,0,1,0],[1,1,0,0]]&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Output:&lt;/strong&gt; 39&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Explanation:&lt;/strong&gt; 0b1111 + 0b1001 + 0b1111 = 15 + 9 + 15 = 39&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;example-2&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#example-2&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Example 2&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input:&lt;/strong&gt; grid = [[0]]&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Output:&lt;/strong&gt; 1&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
